item.title: Time Traveling
item.dc:creator: @kennyboy93 kennyboy93
item.description:
@kennyboy93 wrote:

[quote=“Sleep, post:127, topic:64490”]Time… is just a illusion created by man to depict our daily lives and activities… You come into work one day your boss gets all in your face “You’re late!” - in reality there is no time, just light and dark. So you could come into school 5 minutes or 5 hours late it wouldn’t make a difference.

Time if you think about it doesn’t exist whatsoever, nor will ever. It’s just a measurement of our daily lives and what we do within those lives - which seems like it’s something that the government doesn’t want us to know because they hide up 74.3% of everything they put on the TV… and half the stuff they say isn’t true.[/quote]
Time is a way to pace out your life before you die. It is a way to ensure that things happen in co-ordiantion. What you said is like saying that a street number is an illusion, simply a way of pointing to a place on a street.
Time exists, it’s just intangible.

item.title: Time Traveling
item.dc:creator: @Sleep Sleep
item.description:
@Sleep wrote:

Time… is just a illusion created by man to depict our daily lives and activities… You come into work one day your boss gets all in your face “You’re late!” - in reality there is no time, just light and dark. So you could come into school 5 minutes or 5 hours late it wouldn’t make a difference.

If you were to somehow travel into ‘Time’ you would end up probably seeing a bunch of light and darkness from the rotation of the Earth and Sun. If you could witness the beginning of Earth you would have to fast forward a couple million years to see anything progressing - Like now, if you think back 10 years ago some of us wanted that Power Range or something now it’s all about who has the better iPod, who has the better Cell Phone, material possessions which in turn are constant reminders of ‘Time’.

Time if you think about it doesn’t exist whatsoever, nor will ever. It’s just a measurement of our daily lives and what we do within those lives - which seems like it’s something that the government doesn’t want us to know because they hide up 74.3% of everything they put on the TV… and half the stuff they say isn’t true.

Read full topic
